data: {"index":0,"blockType":"text","finalContent":"---\n\n## OpenAgentic Infrastructure Health Audit\n\n**Audit Timestamp:** 2026-02-21T00:22 UTC\n\n---\n\n### Executive Summary\n\nThe platform is **partially degraded**. The Admin MCP backend is experiencing a persistent internal error (`Attempt to overwrite 'args' in LogRecord`) blocking all database and system-test health checks. Four Prometheus scrape targets remain down — a pattern unchanged across your previous three audits. Flowise remains unhealthy. Core orchestration (LangGraph, CrewAI) and 50 of 54 Prometheus targets are operational.\n\n---\n\n### Primary Health Checks\n\n| # | Subsystem | Tool | Status | Detail |\n|---|-----------|------|:------:|--------|\n| 1 | **Full System Test** | `admin_full_system_test` | ❌ Error | HTTP 500 — `LogRecord` overwrite bug in Admin MCP |\n| 2 | **PostgreSQL** | `admin_system_postgres_health_check` | ❌ Error | Same Admin MCP internal error |\n| 3 | **Redis** | `admin_system_redis_health_check` | ❌ Error | Same Admin MCP internal error |\n| 4 | **Milvus** | `admin_system_milvus_health_check` | ❌ Error | Same Admin MCP internal error |\n| 5 | **Kubernetes Cluster** | `k8s_cluster_health` | ❌ No kubeconfig | Client init failed — no config found |\n| 6 | **Prometheus** | `prometheus_health_summary` | ⚠️ 50 up / 4 down | See target breakdown below |\n\n---\n\n### Supplemental Checks\n\n| Subsystem | Tool | Status | Detail |\n|-----------|------|:------:|--------|\n| **Infrastructure Health** | `admin_system_infrastructure_health_check` | ❌ Error | Same `LogRecord` bug |\n| **LangGraph** | `get_framework_status` | ✅ Healthy | `openagentic-langgraph:3100` |\n| **CrewAI** | `get_framework_status` | ✅ Healthy | `openagentic-crewai:3200` |\n| **Flowise** | `get_framework_status` | ❌ Unhealthy | `openagentic-api:8000/api/flowise-workspace` |\n| **Application Errors (Loki)** | `loki_search_errors` | ✅ Clean | No errors in last 1h |\n| **Firing Alerts** | `prometheus_alerts` | ✅ None | 0 firing, 0 pending |\n\n---\n\n### Prometheus Target Breakdown\n\n| Target | Endpoint | Status | Likely Cause |\n|--------|----------|:------:|--------------|\n| **kube-state-metrics** | `kube-state-metrics.kube-system:8080` | ❌ Down | Pod crash or service mesh issue |\n| **kubernetes-apiservers** | `10.2.10.131:6443` | ❌ Down | API server unreachable from Prometheus |\n| **kubernetes-pods** | `10.42.5.19:8080` | ❌ Down | Application pod down |\n| **kubernetes-pods** | `10.42.2.37:8090` | ❌ Down | Application pod down |\n\n**Prometheus Metrics:**\n\n| Metric | Value | Assessment |\n|--------|------:|:----------:|\n| **Targets UP** | 50 | ✅ |\n| **Targets DOWN** | 4 | ❌ |\n| **Firing Alerts** | 0 | ⚠️ Should be >0 given 4 down targets |\n| **HTTP Request Rate (5m)** | 1.795 req/s | ✅ Normal (up from 0.363 in previous audit) |\n| **Error Rate (5m)** | 0 | ✅ |\n| **Active Sessions** | 0 | ⚠️ Zero at audit time |\n\n---\n\n### MCP Server Registry\n\n| MCP Server | Status | Primary Tools |\n|------------|:------:|---------------|\n| **oap-azure-mcp** | ✅ Registered | `azure_arm_execute`, `azure_graph_execute`, `azure_cost_query` |\n| **oap-aws-mcp** | ✅ Registered | `call_aws`, `aws_identity`, `aws_list_ec2` |\n| **oap-web-mcp** | ✅ Registered | `web_search`, `web_fetch`, `web_news_search` |\n| **oap-flowise-mcp** | ✅ Registered | `flowise_list_chatflows`, `flowise_create_agentflow` |\n| **oap-diagram-mcp** | ✅ Registered | `create_diagram` |\n| **oap-admin-mcp** | ❌ Error | `system_health`, `user_list`, `audit_logs` |\n| **oap-memory-mcp** | ✅ Registered | `memory_store`, `memory_recall`, `memory_search` |\n| **oap-knowledge-mcp** | ✅ Registered | `suggest_tools_for_task`, `list_available_mcps` |\n\n---\n\n### Trend Comparison (vs. Previous Audits)\n\n| Subsystem | Previous Audit | This Audit | Trend |\n|-----------|:--------------:|:----------:|:-----:|\n| **Admin MCP** | ❌ Failed | ❌ Failed (new error) | ⚠️ Different error signature |\n| **Kubernetes MCP** | ❌ No kubeconfig | ❌ No kubeconfig | ➡️ Persistent |\n| **Prometheus UP/DOWN** | 50 / 4 | 50 / 4 | ➡️ Same 4 targets |\n| **HTTP Rate (5m)** | 0.363 req/s | 1.795 req/s | ↗️ **5× increase** |\n| **Error Rate (5m)** | Unavailable | 0 | ✅ Improved visibility |\n| **Loki errors (1h)** | 0 | 0 | ✅ Stable |\n| **Flowise** | ❌ Unhealthy | ❌ Unhealthy | ➡️ Persistent |\n| **LangGraph / CrewAI** | ✅ / ✅ | ✅ / ✅ | ➡️ Stable |\n| **Loki connectivity** | ❌ ECONNREFUSED | ✅ Responding | ↗️ Improved |\n| **Alert Config** | 0 firing (missing) | 0 firing (still missing) | ⚠️ No alerting for down targets |\n\n---\n\n### Findings & Recommendations\n\n| # | Finding | Priority | Recommendation |\n|---|---------|:--------:|----------------|\n| 1 | **Admin MCP internal error** — `Attempt to overwrite 'args' in LogRecord` is a Python logging bug, likely in the MCP's structured logging config. All 5 admin tools fail. | **P0** | Inspect `oap-admin-mcp` container logs. Likely a conflicting `LogRecord` attribute in a logging formatter or handler. Restart the pod after patching the logging config. |\n| 2 | **Flowise unhealthy** — persistent across 3+ audits | **P1** | Investigate Flowise workspace proxy at `openagentic-api:8000/api/flowise-workspace`. Check upstream Flowise pod health and network policy. |\n| 3 | **4 Prometheus targets down** — unchanged across all audits | **P1** | These are stale: `kube-state-metrics`, API server, and 2 pods (`10.42.5.19:8080`, `10.42.2.37:8090`). Either fix the targets or remove stale scrape configs to reduce noise. |\n| 4 | **No alerting rules firing** despite 4 down targets | **P2** | Prometheus has no active alert rules for target health. Add `up == 0` alert rules to ensure visibility. |\n| 5 | **Kubernetes MCP has no kubeconfig** — persistent | **P2** | Mount a valid kubeconfig or configure in-cluster auth for the K8s MCP server. |\n| 6 | **HTTP request rate 5× higher** than previous audit | **Info** | Positive trend — indicates increased platform usage. Monitor for capacity implications. |\n\n> [!WARNING]\n> **Critical blocker:** The Admin MCP failure prevents all database health checks (PostgreSQL, Redis, Milvus) and the full system test. Until this is resolved, backend data-layer health is **unobservable** through platform tooling. The `LogRecord` overwrite error suggests a Python logging misconfiguration introduced in a recent deployment — check the latest revision of the `oap-admin-mcp` deployment."}

